{
  "document_id": "col-38",
  "title": "Colossians 38",
  "type": "scripture",
  "translation": "NRSVue",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "block_id": "col-38-1",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 1,
      "text": "Honor physicians for their services,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-38-2",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 2,
      "text": "for their gift of healing comes from the Most High,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-38-3",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 3,
      "text": "The skill of physicians makes them distinguished,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-38-4",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 4,
      "text": "The Lord created medicines out of the earth,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-38-5",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 5,
      "text": "Was not water made sweet with a tree"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-38-6",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 6,
      "text": "And he gave skill to human beings"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-38-7",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 7,
      "text": "By them the physician heals and takes away pain;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-38-8",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 8,
      "text": "the pharmacist makes a mixture from them."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-38-9",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 9,
      "text": "My child, when you are ill, do not delay,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-38-10",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 10,
      "text": "Give up your faults and direct your hands rightly,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-38-11",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 11,
      "text": "Offer a sweet-smelling sacrifice and a memorial portion of choice flour,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-38-12",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 12,
      "text": "Then give physicians their place, for the Lord created them;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-38-13",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 13,
      "text": "There may come a time when recovery lies in the hands of physicians,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-38-14",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 14,
      "text": "for they, too, pray to the Lord"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-38-15",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 15,
      "text": "Those who sin against their Maker"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-38-16",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 16,
      "text": "My child, let your tears fall for the dead,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-38-17",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 17,
      "text": "Let your weeping be bitter and your wailing fervent;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-38-18",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 18,
      "text": "For grief may result in death,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-38-19",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 19,
      "text": "In calamity, grief continues,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-38-20",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 20,
      "text": "Do not give your heart to grief;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-38-21",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 21,
      "text": "Do not forget, there is no coming back;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-38-22",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 22,
      "text": "Remember his fate, for yours is like it;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-38-23",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 23,
      "text": "When the dead are at rest, let their remembrance rest, too,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-38-24",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 24,
      "text": "The wisdom of the scribe depends on the opportunity of leisure;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-38-25",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 25,
      "text": "How can one become wise who handles the plow"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-38-26",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 26,
      "text": "He sets his heart on plowing furrows,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-38-27",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 27,
      "text": "So it is with every artisan and master artisan"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-38-28",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 28,
      "text": "So it is with the smith sitting by the anvil,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-38-29",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 29,
      "text": "So it is with the potter sitting at his work"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-38-30",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 30,
      "text": "He molds the clay with his arm"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-38-31",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 31,
      "text": "All these rely on their hands,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-38-32",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 32,
      "text": "Without them no city can be inhabited,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-38-33",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 33,
      "text": "nor do they attain eminence in the public assembly."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-38-34",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 34,
      "text": "But they maintain the fabric of the world,"
    }
  ]
}